SIMPLE: heartily
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Heartily
<hw>Heart"i*ly</hw> <pr>(h⟦aum⟧rt"⟦icr⟧*l⟦ycr⟧)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos>
<ety>[From <er>Hearty</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>From the heart; with
all the heart; with sincerity.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I <qex>heartily</qex> forgive them.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>With zeal; actively; vigorously; willingly;
cordially; <as>as, he <ex>heartily</ex> assisted the
prince</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>To eat heartily</b></col>, <cd>to eat freely and with
relish.</cd> <rj><au>Addison.</au></rj></cs></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Sincerely; cordially; zealously; vigorously;
actively; warmly; eagerly; ardently; earnestly.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 679 pr=JMD --></p>

<p><ent>Heartiness</ent>⟦br⟧
